{title: Withered Roses}
{artist: George Morgan}
{composer: Written by Paul Koy}

[G]I found some withered [D7]roses
In an old treasure chest of [G]mine
And more than one su[D7]pposes
They brought to life and love di[G]vine
In those sweet withered [D7]roses
There lives a fragrant breath of [G]June
And in their withered soul re[D7]poses
A love that died too [G]soon
How I [C]long for happy hours
Those [G]golden times once more
Where the [C]roses twine themselves
With [A7]love around the [D7]door
